  "project": "Reproduce one of the lab's recent published analyses from the paper and public data, then extend it: wrap it as an installable, tested, containerized pipeline that runs in one command. Send the repo with a note saying you rebuilt their result and made it reproducible. For a new PI trying to establish a computational group, that is close to irresistible.",
  "email": "Subject: Reproduced your [paper] analysis as a packaged pipeline — UCSD BioE/Math-CS grad\n\nDear Dr. Sinha,\n\nI'm a UC San Diego senior finishing B.S. degrees in Bioengineering: Biotechnology and Mathematics-Computer Science this September. I read [paper] and reimplemented the core analysis from the methods and public data, then packaged it as a containerized, tested pipeline that reproduces end-to-end in one command: [GitHub link]. Notes on the two places I had to guess at parameters are in the README.\n\nI'm a software engineer first — two apps shipped to the App Store, automated CI/CD, containerized Linux infrastructure I run myself — with genomics coursework behind it (Bioinformatic Algorithms, Biological Databases, Machine Learning) and an RNA structure-scoring tool built in a shared repo.\n\nIf you're building out computational capacity in a new lab, I'd value 20 minutes to talk about whether I could be useful. Available full-time from the fall.\n\nBest regards,\nSuraj Laddagiri\nportfolio.sladdagiri.org",
