  "email": "Subject: Bioinformatics Analyst — UCSD BioE/Math-CS grad with pipeline engineering background\n\nDear Dr. Michael,\n\nI'm a UC San Diego senior finishing B.S. degrees in Bioengineering: Biotechnology and Mathematics–Computer Science this September, writing about bioinformatics analyst positions in your lab.\n\nI build maintainable software. I've shipped two applications to the App Store and run automated CI/CD, and I've applied that to genomics coursework: local alignment implemented from scratch with a proper CLI in CSE 182, and an RNA sequence-and-structure scoring tool built collaboratively in a shared Git repository for BENG 202. I've packaged the latter as an installable, tested, containerized Nextflow workflow that reproduces end-to-end on a clean machine: [GitHub link].\n\nI'd welcome the chance to talk about what the lab needs.\n\nBest regards,\nSuraj Laddagiri\nportfolio.sladdagiri.org",
