  "email": "Subject: ML + genomics — UCSD BioE/Math-CS grad, PRS evaluation project\n\nDear Dr. Torkamani,\n\nI'm a UC San Diego senior finishing B.S. degrees in Bioengineering: Biotechnology and Mathematics–Computer Science this September, writing about research software and analysis roles in your group.\n\nMy coursework sits at the intersection you work in — Machine Learning, Natural Language Processing, Computer Vision, Bioinformatic Algorithms and Biological Databases — and I've built at that intersection too: an RNA sequence-and-structure scoring pipeline for BENG 202, and a 535-model transformer classifier with a real-time web front end for a course project.\n\nTo engage with your area I built a polygenic risk score from public summary statistics and focused the analysis on calibration and stratified performance across ancestry groups rather than headline AUC, since that seems to be where these models actually break: [GitHub link].\n\nWould you have 20 minutes?\n\nBest regards,\nSuraj Laddagiri\nportfolio.sladdagiri.org",
