  "email": "Subject: Imaging analysis pipelines — UCSD BioE/Math-CS grad\n\nDear Dr. Nimmerjahn,\n\nI'm a UC San Diego senior finishing B.S. degrees in Bioengineering: Biotechnology and Mathematics–Computer Science this September, writing about computational positions in the center.\n\nI work on real-time visual tracking: I shipped an iOS navigation aid for blind users that runs ARKit SLAM over fused camera, LiDAR and IMU data and replans in under a second on-device, and I've taken Computer Vision. Imaging in behaving animals seemed like the same class of problem — signal extraction under motion — so I built a motion-correction and ROI-extraction pipeline for a public calcium imaging dataset and benchmarked it against CaImAn for both accuracy and runtime: [GitHub link].\n\nWould you have 20 minutes?\n\nBest regards,\nSuraj Laddagiri\nportfolio.sladdagiri.org",
